# Rush publish-time registry — used by: rush publish --publish
#
# Publishing uses npm Trusted Publishers (OIDC). The GitHub Actions release
# workflow authenticates with a short-lived OIDC token, so NO auth token is
# configured here — an `_authToken` line (even an empty one) would suppress the
# OIDC flow. Requirements, all handled by .github/workflows/release.yml:
#   - the job grants `permissions: id-token: write`
#   - npm >= 11.5.1 (the workflow upgrades npm; node 20 ships an older npm)
#   - a Trusted Publisher is configured on npmjs.com for each @yoltra package,
#     pointing at this repo + workflow (release.yml)
#
# For a local dry run against Verdaccio, override the registry at call time:
#   rush publish --publish --registry http://localhost:4873
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
